Overall Assessment
The repo has made strong progress through domain models, loaders, unit tests, fixtures, API basics, and CP-SAT integration. The biggest architectural drift is in the solver/explainability layer: planning selection semantics, specialty activation, rule statuses, and infeasible extraction no longer fully match the original backend-first design.

The most urgent inconsistency is not a missing feature but a trust issue: results can look explainable while being derived from candidate/model metadata rather than the actual solved assignment.